pr_title: Octave calculation fix for scale degree block (nth modal pitch)
pr_body:
- Defined a new variable `deltaSemi` alongside `deltaOctave` which looks for changes in Octave that we play and adapts according to the key selected.

- `deltaOctave` calculates changes in reference octave which occur a semitone before the key selected.

- Fixes #2238

pr_body:
This patch adds the following stuff:

- A (true) scale degree block

- `scaledegreeout` as an outType. I wonder if it has any more use cases but we have it now just in case. It is essentially combination of a number and an accidental.

Work:

- [x] New output type: `scaledegreeout`
- [x] New pie menu 

**Comments:** I did not create a separate function for the pie menu of this block, rather I adjusted the existing function for solfege and the inputs accordingly.

- [x] Seven note frameworks 
- [x] Sub-heptatonic frameworks without any chromatic undertone
- [x] Sub-heptatonic frameworks with chromatic undertone
- [x] Peculiar scales like `whole tone` and `fibonacci`

**Comments:** Whole tone is still a little weird in terms of what output you would expect and what output a mathematical function would generate. More on that in comments.

- [x] Pitch Preview i.e note playing on selection.

**Comments:** I adjusted the current pie menu function for solfege etc. to map numeric values to solfege and process notes accordingly. Major fixture might be in order if we implement a solution for #1957 , after which key signature would be available beforehand.

- [x] Note processing final check remains

**Comments:** Works fine in my initial tests. Further inputs required from @pikurasa 

- [ ] Little housekeeping stuff like updating block labels etc. fluctuates at times. 

**Comments :** Working on this. ~~Somehow a separate name for the block doesn't seem to be functional.~~ Will provide details in the comment.
Add a claret over block label. e.g:  



Will fix #2058

This commit adds some basic linting rules. 

- Upgraded ESLint, added some basic rules in `eslintrc` and added a `babel-eslint` parser to avoid some errors related to ES6 JS.

- To bring all current code to specified standards, a lot of files would change, so this would need to be planned to avoid merge conflicts.
